	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f966546018411><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Clerics</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=392><span id= >Durnhelm</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>14 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 5:00 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;     Well as I have just read it speaks of Cleric's concentrating on healing. I agree totally. Unless theirs 3 or 4 healers in a group, or your possibly fighting undead, theirs totally no reason for a Cleric to do anything but heal. Leave that job for the Wizards. Also remember, undead are an exception, where a good cleric can play the role of a nuker when fighting the undead. Also remember that after 49 or so Clerics can res themeselves and in effect lose almost no experience. Guess thats a bout it, later.<br>&nbsp;<br>Durnhelm Eorling <br>"All that is gold does not glitter"<br>57 Wizard,<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
